# Multi-Model Routing

When selecting a model for a task:

1. Read `models/routing.yaml` for tier definitions
2. Match task type to the appropriate tier
3. Use the primary model; fall back in order if unavailable
4. Respect cost controls in `models/routing.yaml`

## Tier Quick Reference

| Tier | Primary | Use Case |
|------|---------|----------|
| reasoning_deep | Claude Opus 4.6 | Architecture, critical decisions |
| reasoning_fast | Claude Sonnet 4.6 | Default coding |
| cheap_fast | Claude Haiku 4.5 | Completion, boilerplate |
| long_context | Gemini 3.1 Pro | Full codebase analysis (2M) |
| code_specialist | Codestral 25 | Code gen and review |
| vision | Claude Opus 4.6 | Screenshot/design to code |
| local_only | Llama 3.3 70B | Air-gapped, zero cost |

## Provider Priority
1. Anthropic (Claude)
2. Google (Gemini)
3. OpenAI (GPT)
4. OpenRouter (300+ models)
5. Ollama (local, free)
